The paper focuses on the design and development of big data systems, which involves choosing appropriate storage and computing infrastructures. This falls under the category of database systems (cs.DB) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the requirements and characteristics of different applications, which is related to software engineering (cs.SE) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper analyzes and categorizes different NoSQL solutions, which is related to information retrieval (cs.IR).
